---
const titles = [
  {
    src: '/assets/identity-thumbs/duelcasters.png',
    kicker: 'The first game',
    name: 'DuelCasters of SpellRealms',
    href: 'https://duelcasters.spellrealms.com',
    description: 'Two casters. One board. Every word a weapon. Step into the dueling halls and prove your command of the arcane.',
  },
  {
    src: '/assets/identity-thumbs/realms.png',
    kicker: 'Coming next',
    name: 'Realms of SpellRealms',
    href: 'https://realms.spellrealms.com',
    description: 'Beyond the spires lie territories unmapped and civilizations older than the written word. The journey outward begins here.',
  },
  {
    src: '/assets/identity-thumbs/spires.png',
    kicker: 'On the horizon',
    name: 'Spires of SpellRealms',
    href: 'https://spires.spellrealms.com',
    description: 'At the heart of SpellRealms\'s greatest cities, towers reach into clouds of pure arcane energy. Some say those who climb high enough never return the same.',
  },
];
---

<section id="world" class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-24 pb-0">
  <!-- Heading -->
  <div class="mb-8 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs font-black" style="color: #f5ce82;">The world</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 mb-4 text-[clamp(2.1rem,5vw,4.25rem)] leading-[0.98]">
      Ancient power. Rival orders.<br />Realms shaped by language itself.
    </h2>
    <p>
      Long before kingdoms rose and fell, the first mages of SpellRealms discovered that language, spoken with precision and intent, could reshape reality. They built orders around that mystery. They raised towers to study it. They went to war over it. That war never truly ended — it simply moved into the dueling halls, the academies, and the hidden vaults beneath the great spires. Its echoes still move through SpellRealms.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Hero lore panel -->
  <div
    class="relative w-full overflow-hidden mb-5"
    style="border-radius: 28px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); min-height: 480px; box-shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.45);"
  >
    <img
      src="/assets/generated/spellandria-hero-world.jpg"
      alt="The luminous spires of SpellRealms rise above a divided realm"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center absolute inset-0"
      style="min-height: 480px;"
    />
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0"
      style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(8,5,12,0.86) 0%, rgba(8,5,12,0.3) 50%, rgba(8,5,12,0.7) 100%);"
      aria-hidden="true"
    ></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 p-8 md:p-12 max-w-lg">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs font-black mb-3" style="color: #f5ce82;">Lore</p>
      <h3 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-4">The age of the luminous spires</h3>
      <p>
        The great spires were not built — they were grown, fed by centuries of concentrated arcane inscription. Each one is a living library, a fortress, and a beacon. The order that controls a spire controls the flow of magical knowledge across an entire region. Control enough of them, and you control the world. No one has ever controlled enough of them. Not yet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Game title cards -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5 mb-5">
    {titles.map(t => (
      <a
        href={t.href}
        class="overflow-hidden no-underline transition-transform duration-150 hover:-translate-y-1"
        style="border-radius: 28px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); background: rgba(14,10,20,0.82); backdrop-filter: blur(18px); box-shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(0,0,0,0.45); display: block;"
      >
        <div class="h-56 overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src={t.src}
            alt={t.name}
            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="p-6">
          <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs font-black mb-2" style="color: #f5ce82;">{t.kicker}</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl mb-2">{t.name}</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">{t.description}</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-bold mt-4" style="color: #f5ce82;">Visit game page →</p>
        </div>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <!-- Lore panels -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 mb-0">
    <article
      class="p-8"
      style="border-radius: 28px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); background: rgba(14,10,20,0.82); backdrop-filter: blur(18px);"
    >
      <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs font-black mb-3" style="color: #f5ce82;">The arcane mystery</p>
      <h3 class="text-2xl mb-3">To speak is to cast</h3>
      <p>Every word in SpellRealms carries a resonance — a frequency of intention that, when shaped correctly, becomes force. Casters spend lifetimes learning to feel the weight of a word before they speak it. In a duel, there is no time for hesitation. You trace the word into existence, you commit to its meaning, and you hold nothing back.</p>
    </article>
    <article
      class="p-8"
      style="border-radius: 28px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); background: rgba(14,10,20,0.82); backdrop-filter: blur(18px); background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 80% 0%, rgba(141,114,255,0.14), transparent 28%);"
    >
      <p class="uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-xs font-black mb-3" style="color: #f5ce82;">The orders</p>
      <h3 class="text-2xl mb-3">A world of rival traditions</h3>
Every word in SpellRealms carries a charge — but no one city, order, or bloodline fully agrees on how that power works. Some treat language as music. Others treat it as architecture. Still others believe it behaves like weather, memory, or fire.
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
